"use strict";(self.webpackChunkhalt_website=self.webpackChunkhalt_website||[]).push([[44068],{15271:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"tag":{"label":"guinea pig","permalink":"/docs/tags/guinea-pig","allTagsPath":"/docs/tags","count":29,"items":[{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bloat-in-guinea-pigs","title":"Bloat in Guinea Pigs","description":"Bloat, also known as Gastric Dilatation and Volvulus (GDV), is a sudden, life-threatening condition that can affect guinea pigs. It occurs when the stomach fills with gas and, in some cases, twists on itself (volvulus), cutting off blood supply to the stomach and other organs. This is a severe medical emergency that requires immediate veterinary intervention. Understanding the signs and acting quickly can be the difference between life and death.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bloat-in-guinea-pigs"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bordetella-in-guinea-pigs","title":"Bordetella in Guinea Pigs","description":"Bordetella bronchiseptica is a bacterium that causes respiratory disease in a variety of animals. While it is most commonly known as a cause of \'kennel cough\' in dogs, it can be a life-threatening...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bordetella-in-guinea-pigs"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/cl","title":"Caseous/Cervical Lymphadenitis in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pigs are beloved pets known for their friendly and gentle nature, but like all animals, they can be susceptible to a variety of health issues. One condition that can affect them is Caseous Lymphadenitis (CL), a bacterial infection that causes swelling and abscesses in the lymph nodes. This disease can be serious and requires prompt treatment to avoid complications.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/cl"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/safety/dangerous-treats-and-toys","title":"Dangerous Treats and Toys for Guinea Pigs","description":"As a loving guinea pig owner, it\u2019s natural to want to spoil your pet with tasty treats and fun toys. However, it is critically important to know that many common foods and pet store items can be...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/safety/dangerous-treats-and-toys"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/dental-disease","title":"Dental Disease in Guinea Pigs","description":"Dental disease is one of the most common and serious health problems affecting guinea pigs. Unlike humans, a guinea pig\'s teeth grow continuously throughout their life. This continuous growth can...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/dental-disease"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/essential-supplies","title":"Essential Supplies for Guinea Pigs: A Helping All Little Things Guide","description":"Bringing home a guinea pig (or better yet\u2014a pair!) is an exciting and joyful experience. To set your new friends up for a happy, healthy life, it\u2019s important to have the right supplies ready from day...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/essential-supplies"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/eye-health","title":"Eye Health and Vision Issues in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pig eyes are large, bright, and positioned on the sides of their head, giving them a wide field of vision to watch for predators. While generally robust, their eyes are susceptible to a range...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/eye-health"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fetal-arrhythmia","title":"Fetal Arrhythmia in Guinea Pigs: What It Is and What It Means","description":"Pregnancy in guinea pigs can be a delicate time, requiring close monitoring and appropriate veterinary care. One rare but important condition that can arise is fetal arrhythmia, an irregular heartbeat detected in a developing fetus. While unsettling to hear about, understanding this condition can help owners and rescues make informed decisions.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fetal-arrhythmia"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fleas","title":"Fleas in Guinea Pigs: Causes, Symptoms, Treatment, and Prevention","description":"Fleas are common parasites that can affect various pets, including guinea pigs. While these small, wingless insects are more frequently associated with cats and dogs, a flea infestation can cause...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fleas"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fly-strike","title":"Fly Strike in Guinea Pigs","description":"Fly strike, also known as myiasis, is a serious and often fatal condition that affects guinea pigs. It occurs when flies lay their eggs on a guinea pig, and the hatching maggots begin to feed on the...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fly-strike"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/grooming-your-guinea-pig","title":"Grooming Your Guinea Pig","description":"Grooming is an essential part of responsible guinea pig care that goes beyond just keeping them looking their best. Regular grooming sessions are an excellent opportunity to bond with your pet and...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/grooming-your-guinea-pig"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/guineapigcare","title":"Guinea Pig Care","description":"Plain, quality pellets are best for guinea pigs. Guinea pigs under 6 months old should be fed an Alfalfa pellet and hay-based diet. Do not feed your guinea pig any food with artificial coloring,...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/guineapigcare"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/guineapigpoop","title":"Guinea Pig Poop","description":"Guinea pigs have sensitive digestive systems, and looking at their poop is the best way to quickly determine how your guinea pig\'s system is functioning. It\'s also one of the reasons why it\'s so...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/guineapigpoop"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/home-health-care","title":"Home Health Care for Your Guinea Pig: A Helping All Little Things Guide","description":"Guinea pigs are hardy little creatures, but they rely on attentive caregivers to keep them healthy and comfortable. Performing regular home health checks is one of the most important things you can...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/home-health-care"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/is-a-guinea-pig-right-for-me","title":"Is a Guinea Pig Right for Me and My Family?","description":"Guinea pigs are gentle, social, and surprisingly communicative little animals \u2014 and they are one of the most rewarding small pets you can share your home with. But like any pet, they come with real...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/is-a-guinea-pig-right-for-me"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/know-your-guinea-pig-breeds","title":"Know Your Guinea Pig Breeds","description":"From the sleek and smooth to the curly and long-haired, guinea pigs come in a wonderful variety of breeds, each with its own unique look and grooming needs. While personality is individual, some...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/know-your-guinea-pig-breeds"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/lymphoma","title":"Lymphoma","description":"Lymphoma is a type of cancer that affects the lymphatic system, and while it may be rare in guinea pigs, it\u2019s a serious health condition that pet owners should be aware of. Early detection of lymphoma can significantly improve the chances of managing the disease and providing your guinea pig with a better quality of life. Understanding the nature of lymphoma, recognizing the early signs, and seeking timely veterinary care are crucial steps in ensuring the best possible outcome for your guinea pig.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/lymphoma"},{"id":"general-care/mastitis","title":"Mastitis in Small Pets","description":"An overview of mastitis, a painful infection of the mammary glands, in small pets. Learn to recognize the signs, understand the causes, and know when to seek immediate veterinary care.","permalink":"/docs/general-care/mastitis"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/nutrition-information","title":"Nutrition Information for Guinea Pigs","description":"A balanced and appropriate diet is the single most important factor in maintaining the health and well-being of your guinea pig. Unlike many other small pets, guinea pigs have specific and unique...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/nutrition-information"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/ovariancysts","title":"Ovarian Cysts","description":"Ovarian cysts are a common health issue in female guinea pigs, especially as they age. These fluid-filled sacs form on the ovaries and can lead to discomfort and health complications if untreated. Here\u2019s everything you need to know about detecting, treating, and preventing ovarian cysts in guinea pigs, as well as why the flank approach is often preferred for surgical removal.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/ovariancysts"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/proper-handling-of-guinea-pigs","title":"Proper Handling of Guinea Pigs","description":"Proper handling is fundamental to building a trusting relationship with your guinea pig and ensuring their safety. As prey animals, guinea pigs can be naturally skittish and may be frightened by...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/proper-handling-of-guinea-pigs"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/satinsyndrome","title":"Satin Syndrome in Guinea Pigs","description":"\u2705 Download our checklist here and bring it to your vet! \u2705","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/satinsyndrome"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/sexing-guinea-pigs","title":"Sexing Guinea Pigs","description":"Correctly identifying the sex of a guinea pig is a crucial skill for any owner, breeder, or rescue. It is the only way to prevent accidental and unwanted pregnancies, which can be dangerous for...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/sexing-guinea-pigs"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/getting-started/the-ideal-guinea-pig-habitat","title":"The Ideal Guinea Pig Habitat","description":"Creating a safe, spacious, and enriching environment is one of the most important responsibilities of a guinea pig owner. The right habitat directly impacts their physical health and mental...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/getting-started/the-ideal-guinea-pig-habitat"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/clubbed-feet","title":"Understanding Clubbed Feet and Limb Deformities in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pigs are known for their sweet personalities and unique charm\u2014but some arrive into rescue with visible physical challenges, including limb deformities commonly referred to as \\"clubbed feet.\\" Understanding this condition is key to providing these special-needs pigs with the quality of life they deserve.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/clubbed-feet"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/coat-color-genetics","title":"Understanding Guinea Pig Coat Color Genetics","description":"Guinea pigs are known for their stunning diversity of coat colors and patterns, from solid black to intricate brindles and dalmatians. This variety isn\'t random; it\'s the result of a fascinating and complex world of genetics. Understanding the basics of coat color inheritance is not only interesting for curious owners but is also critical for responsible breeding and rescue advocacy to prevent serious genetic health problems.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/coat-color-genetics"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/lethalwhite","title":"Understanding Lethal White Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pigs are beloved companions known for their sweet nature, vocal personalities, and varied appearances. But within the world of guinea pig care, there\u2019s a little-known and serious condition that deserves more awareness\u2014lethal white syndrome.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/lethalwhite"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/urinary-bladder","title":"Urinary and Bladder Issues in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pigs may be small, but they have complex needs\u2014and that includes their urinary health. Bladder and urinary tract issues are common in guinea pigs and can range from mild to life-threatening....","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/urinary-bladder"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/hairless-skinny-pigs","title":"What to Know about Hairless or \\"Skinny\\" Pigs","description":"Hairless guinea pigs, most commonly known as \\"Skinny Pigs,\\" are a unique and increasingly popular variety of cavy. Their striking appearance, lacking the typical fluffy coat, makes them stand out, but it also means they have specialized care requirements that potential owners must be prepared to meet. Understanding their unique needs is essential to providing them with a healthy and happy life.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/breeds-and-genetics/hairless-skinny-pigs"}],"unlisted":false}}')}}]);